## Project Context

- This repository defines and evolves the **Write Up** concept: a long-term AI writing mentor for students and aspiring writers.
- Primary docs live in `docs/`. Treat these as the source of truth for product intent and team framing.
- See `product-vision.md` for the full product vision and HMW statement context.
- See `docs/problem-framing-canvas.md` for constraints, affected user groups, and equity-centered framing.
- See `architecture/architecture.md` for the system architecture and consolidation plan.

## Product Goals To Preserve

- Prioritize **learning and mastery over instant correction**.
- Focus on identifying recurring patterns across writing (syntax, tone, vocabulary), not only one-off fixes.
- Preserve user voice and dialect; avoid suggestions that homogenize writing style.
- Prefer "teach me why" and guided practice loops over "rewrite this for me" behavior.
- Keep multilingual, dyslexic, and dialect-diverse users in scope when proposing features or copy.

## Conventions For This Repo

- Keep files and folders lowercase with hyphen-separated names (e.g., `problem-framing-canvas.md`).
- Use Markdown for project artifacts; keep headings concise and progressively structured (`#`, `##`, `###`).
- Write in plain language; define jargon on first use.
- When adding or updating strategy docs, link to existing docs instead of duplicating large source text.
- Keep changes focused and incremental; preserve existing intent and terminology unless explicitly revised.

## AI Collaboration Guidelines

- Before proposing implementation details, anchor recommendations to product goals and constraints above.
- When suggesting UI/feature ideas, include:
  - the user learning outcome,
  - how voice preservation is protected,
  - and how the idea avoids becoming a pure auto-rewriter.
- If requirements are ambiguous, ask clarifying questions instead of filling gaps with generic assumptions.
- Prefer concrete, actionable outputs (checklists, structured sections, draft language) over vague summaries.
